reviews.reviewText: Very cute and my baby loves it but it doesn't stay wrapped around the car seat handle long. It comes loose and slides around. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars This is Great for a Car Seat
reviews.reviewText: This is a really cute addition to a car seat to keep your baby occupied. I like the colors and the shape. I think it is priced a bit high for the quality of the product. But I do think it is worth checking out and making your own opinion.

I think that the true test of a toy like this is if it keeps the baby entertained and that they are attracted to it. A full five stars for this toy. We use the car seat in the stroller. Thus this toy is there for both the car and the stroller. Our baby is particularly attracted to the donut ring with the balls inside.Pros:- good quality- unique wrap around design which keeps this toy securely fastened to the handle of the car seat- colourful- baby is attracted to the hanging pieces and can reach up and touch them- Not noisy so when driving they are not distractingCons:- noneOverall I can highly recommend this.

reviews.reviewTitle: Cute- Read the description about why it is in black and white.
reviews.reviewText: I thought this was OK for baby's first present. But it does look a bit dull- almost all black and white. She loves it and is perfect for trips in the vehicle or out for a stroll

reviews.reviewTitle: Colours are vibrant, well made but scrunches up
reviews.reviewText: It’s well made but scrunches up when you put it on the car seat. All the hanging things are kind of jumbled together. I thought they would be more spread out..

The materials and stitching are well done and none of the tags feel loose. The dangling toys offer a fun variety that babies love, especially the mirror and the rattle.
